article.description: Brian Sullivan hit six 3-pointers and finished with 20 points and seven assists, and Peyton Aldridge had 13 points and 10 rebounds to help Davidson beat La Salle 79-66 Wednesday night.
article.headline: Sullivan scores 20, Davidson rolls past La Salle 79-66
article.linkText: Sullivan scores 20, Davidson rolls past La Salle 79-66
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Brian Sullivan hit six 3-pointers and finished with 20 points and seven assists, and Peyton Aldridge had 13 points and 10 rebounds to help Davidson beat La Salle 79-66 Wednesday night. Jordan Barham scored 12 on 5-of-7 shooting for Davidson. The Wildcats had a season-high 24 assists on 29 field goals while shooting 58 percent overall, including 12 of 24 from 3-point range. Davidson (14-8, 6-5 Atlantic 10) led by as many as 12 in the first half before going into the break leading 38-31. Sullivan hit three 3s during an 11-4 run to open the second half that made it 49-35 with 17 minutes to play and La Salle (5-17, 1-10) trailed by double figures the rest of the way. Freshman Yevgen Sakhniuk led the Explorers with a season-high 20 points. Jordan Price scored 15 with seven rebounds and six assists.
